"The interest of justice must not be shackled by any boundary or border and justice must be seen to be done without fear or favour," Justice and Correctional Services Minister, Ronald Ramola, said in a statement. The sanctions freeze any assets the three Gupta brothers and their business associate, Salim Essa, have in the US and bars US citizens and businesses from entering into transactions with them. The Guptas were close to Zuma, and were accused of fraudulently acquiring government contracts and trying to influence cabinet appointments to advance their business interests. All the accused have denied any wrongdoing.

--BBC--